          "Disengaged: Largest group and lowest level of activity. students exhibit the lowest course performance.\n\nSurface: Moderate levels of activity, often especially focused on either assessments. In general they have relatively low marks in the course.\n\nActive: 30%  of learners follow this approach. For the final course topic learners increased Information Oriented tactic.\n\nHighly Active: High levels of activity starts using the Long _Diverse Oriented tactic but the tactic use decreases with time, wherein learners in this group also use Video Oriented Tactic. Learners in this strategy have the highet approval rate. ",
